    "Commentary Vol. 77": "And it came to pass in the eleventh year, &c.] Of Zedekiah\u2019s\nreign, and Jehoiachin\u2019s captivity; some little time after the prophecy in\n[v_Ezk_19_1] (<261901>Ezekiel 19:1), here the prophecies come into their order again, being\ninterrupted by those of a much later date, at the end of the preceding\nchapter, and the former part of this:\nin the first month, in the seventh day of the month; the month Nisan, which\nanswers to part of March, and part of April; the seventh day must be about\nthe twenty ninth of March; but, according to Bishop Usherf560, it was on\nthe twenty sixth of April, on the third day of the week (Tuesday), in 3416\nA.M. or before Christ 588: this was given out three months and two days\nbefore Jerusalem was taken:\nthat the word of the Lord came unto me, saying; as follows:\nVer."
